South Africa's IDC Allocates $36 Million to Help Flood, Dought-Hit Farmers

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-03-01T11:59:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/south-africa-s-idc-allocates-36-million-to-help-flood-dought-hit-farmers.html
  South Africa ’s Industrial
Development Corp. said it has made 250 million rand available to
the Landbank to help agricultural businesses that have been
affected by the recent flooding and drought.  “This is part of the 750 million rand flood and drought
relief fund,” the IDC said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
